#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:4
msgid "umask - set or get the file creation mode mask"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:7
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:9
msgid "umask [OPTIONS] [MASK]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:15
msgid "Description"
msgstr "描述"

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:17
msgid ""
"``umask`` displays and manipulates the \"umask\", or file creation mode "
"mask, which is used to restrict the default access to files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:19
msgid ""
"The umask may be expressed either as an octal number, which represents the "
"rights that will be removed by default, or symbolically, which represents "
"the only rights that will be granted by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:21
msgid ""
"Access rights are explained in the manual page for the ``chmod(1)`` program."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:23
msgid ""
"With no parameters, the current file creation mode mask is printed as an "
"octal number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:25
msgid "**-S** or **--symbolic**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:26
msgid "Prints the umask in symbolic form instead of octal form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:28
msgid "**-p** or **--as-command**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:29
msgid "Outputs the umask in a form that may be reused as input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:31
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:32
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr "顯示此指令的幫助資訊。"

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:34
msgid ""
"If a numeric mask is specified as a parameter, the current shell's umask "
"will be set to that value, and the rights specified by that mask will be "
"removed from new files and directories by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:36
msgid ""
"If a symbolic mask is specified, the desired permission bits, and not the "
"inverse, should be specified. A symbolic mask is a comma separated list of "
"rights. Each right consists of three parts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:38
msgid ""
"The first part specifies to whom this set of right applies, and can be one "
"of ``u``, ``g``, ``o`` or ``a``, where ``u`` specifies the user who owns the "
"file, ``g`` specifies the group owner of the file, ``o`` specific other "
"users rights and ``a`` specifies all three should be changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:40
msgid ""
"The second part of a right specifies the mode, and can be one of ``=``, "
"``+`` or ``-``, where ``=`` specifies that the rights should be set to the "
"new value, ``+`` specifies that the specified right should be added to those "
"previously specified and ``-`` specifies that the specified rights should be "
"removed from those previously specified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:42
msgid ""
"The third part of a right specifies what rights should be changed and can be "
"any combination of ``r``, ``w`` and ``x``, representing read, write and "
"execute rights."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:44
msgid ""
"If the first and second parts are skipped, they are assumed to be ``a`` and "
"``=``, respectively. As an example, ``r,u+w`` means all users should have "
"read access and the file owner should also have write access."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:46
msgid "Note that symbolic masks currently do not work as intended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:50
msgid "Example"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/umask.rst:52
msgid ""
"``umask 177`` or ``umask u=rw`` sets the file creation mask to read and "
"write for the owner and no permissions at all for any other users."
msgstr ""
